  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Core Relief Items (CRIs) for Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support the displaced population in Syria living without adequate materials with core relief items (CRIs).  Over 96,600 displaced persons in seven governorates (Aleppo, Rural Damascus, Homs, Idleb, Hassakeh, Dara&#x2019;s, and Damascus) will be provided with CRIs supporting their health and welfare, and preserving their dignity. CRI kits consist of mattresses, blankets, kitchen sets, hygiene kits, diapers etc., for an approximate value of US$ 241.80 each. 

Total project budget: US$36,345,000
Total funds received to date: US$13,926
Amount requested from the CERF: US$5,000,139</narrative>
  </description>
